title: Jeremy Antonisse
text:
Jeremy Antonisse (born 29 March 2002) is a professional <a href="Association%20football">footballer</a> who plays as a <a href="Forward%20%28association%20football%29">forward</a> for <a href="Eerste%20Divisie">Eerste Divisie</a> team <a href="Jong%20PSV">Jong PSV</a> and the <a href="Cura%C3%A7ao%20national%20football%20team">Curaçao national team</a>.
Club career.
A youth academy graduate of <a href="PSV%20Eindhoven">PSV</a>, Antonisse signed his first professional contract with the club in August 2019. He signed a three-year contract through to the summer of 2022.
On 30 November 2020, he made his professional debut for <a href="Jong%20PSV">Jong PSV</a> in a 1–0 league defeat against <a href="SC%20Cambuur">SC Cambuur</a>. He made his senior debut for PSV on 26 January 2021 in a 2–0 <a href="Eredivisie">league</a> win against <a href="FC%20Emmen">FC Emmen</a>. On 23 August 2021, he signed a contract extension with club until June 2024.
International career.
Born in Netherlands, Antonisse is of Curaçaoan descent. He has previously represented Netherlands in youth level. On 16 October 2019, he was named in stand-by list for <a href="2019%20FIFA%20U-17%20World%20Cup">2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup</a> after missing out on 21-man final squad for the tournament.
In March 2021, he received maiden call-up to <a href="Cura%C3%A7ao%20national%20football%20team">Curaçao national team</a> for <a href="2022%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20qualification%20%28CONCACAF%29">World Cup qualifying</a> matches against <a href="Saint%20Vincent%20and%20the%20Grenadines%20national%20football%20team">Saint Vincent and the Grenadines</a> and <a href="Cuba%20national%20football%20team">Cuba</a>. He made his debut on 25 March 2021 against Saint Vincent and the Grenadines. In June 2021, he was named in Curaçao's 42-man preliminary squad for <a href="2021%20CONCACAF%20Gold%20Cup">2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup</a>.
